1
00:00:18,940 --> 00:00:23,880
♪Only after bloom comes fruit♪

2
00:00:25,290 --> 00:00:29,260
♪Who says glory must fade to the past♪

3
00:00:31,920 --> 00:00:37,010
♪Only through thunder
do you reach the clouds♪

4
00:00:38,210 --> 00:00:43,120
♪Who made you the crown of every peak♪

5
00:00:44,650 --> 00:00:47,930
♪I stand at the center of the stage♪

6
00:00:47,930 --> 00:00:51,000
♪My shadow is pinned against the wall♪

7
00:00:51,710 --> 00:00:56,660
♪Facing the light earns every medal♪

8
00:00:57,700 --> 00:01:00,880
♪Little birds,
save your needless pecking♪

9
00:01:00,880 --> 00:01:04,160
♪The open sky rises high♪

10
00:01:04,700 --> 00:01:09,830
♪When night falls,
the moon begins to shine♪

11
00:01:10,600 --> 00:01:13,860
♪I stand in the heart of these lands♪

12
00:01:13,860 --> 00:01:17,220
♪My shadow bears no crown or robe♪

13
00:01:17,630 --> 00:01:23,300
♪Then I know truth needs no disguise♪

14
00:01:23,710 --> 00:01:26,960
♪The green hills see me as I am♪

15
00:01:26,960 --> 00:01:30,290
♪Like dew, lightning,
and moon on the river♪

16
00:01:30,690 --> 00:01:34,730
♪Showing me exactly who I am♪

17
00:01:34,730 --> 00:01:35,980
=The Lead=

18
00:01:36,020 --> 00:01:37,940
=Episode 11=

19
00:01:38,480 --> 00:01:40,880
Here's today's paper.

20
00:01:41,320 --> 00:01:43,880
It has a really important story.

21
00:01:44,880 --> 00:01:47,480
The ban on Hong Hu Chi Wei Dui years ago

22
00:01:47,980 --> 00:01:49,000
has been lifted.

23
00:01:49,220 --> 00:01:50,800
- Great.
- Yes, exactly.

24
00:01:50,800 --> 00:01:51,760
- Exactly.
- Wonderful.

25
00:01:51,760 --> 00:01:53,240
- Huge news.
- This is good news.

26
00:01:53,240 --> 00:01:54,080
What is it?

27
00:01:54,160 --> 00:01:55,960
These model operas can't go on now.

28
00:01:56,560 --> 00:01:59,040
I worried daily about our troupe.

29
00:01:59,160 --> 00:02:00,360
I wondered what we could do.

30
00:02:01,800 --> 00:02:04,160
I needed a nap, and a pillow showed up.

31
00:02:04,400 --> 00:02:05,760
Now, I know exactly where to go.

32
00:02:06,640 --> 00:02:07,480
Well said.

33
00:02:08,040 --> 00:02:10,200
The movie Hong Hu Chi Wei Dui

34
00:02:10,200 --> 00:02:12,840
was an amazing revolutionary film

35
00:02:12,840 --> 00:02:14,640
with song and dance.

36
00:02:15,600 --> 00:02:16,500
Back in those years,

37
00:02:16,500 --> 00:02:18,640
every time I watched it,

38
00:02:18,640 --> 00:02:20,140
I was moved.

39
00:02:20,140 --> 00:02:21,230
Me too.

40
00:02:21,720 --> 00:02:23,200
Too bad it got shut down.

41
00:02:24,400 --> 00:02:25,680
Good thing it's back now.

42
00:02:26,400 --> 00:02:28,040
Deputy Director Zhu and I decided

43
00:02:28,520 --> 00:02:30,280
to rehearse Hong Hu Chi Wei Dui.

44
00:02:30,350 --> 00:02:31,860
Great. Let's do it.

45
00:02:31,860 --> 00:02:33,360
- I believe
- Great.

46
00:02:34,160 --> 00:02:36,880
other County Troupes want it too.

47
00:02:37,880 --> 00:02:40,360
So, we have to beat them to it

48
00:02:40,360 --> 00:02:41,480
and stage this show first.

49
00:02:42,160 --> 00:02:44,840
Our first show has to make a splash.

50
00:02:45,840 --> 00:02:46,720
Are we confident?

51
00:02:46,720 --> 00:02:48,080
Yes!

52
00:02:55,530 --> 00:02:57,280
♪Gunfire rings out all around♪

53
00:02:57,280 --> 00:02:58,920
♪The sky goes dark; the sun goes dim♪

54
00:02:59,000 --> 00:03:01,160
Aren't you the lead? You do it.

55
00:03:01,840 --> 00:03:03,206
- You do it.
- It's a rare chance.

56
00:03:03,480 --> 00:03:04,600
Do you know that?

57
00:03:04,600 --> 00:03:08,910
♪They harm, seize grain,
and burn villages♪

58
00:03:09,160 --> 00:03:12,390
♪Trying to turn Honghu
into a slaughter ground♪

59
00:03:27,160 --> 00:03:29,160
Too windy to watch. Let's leave.

60
00:03:29,320 --> 00:03:30,160
Stop your nonsense.

61
00:03:30,280 --> 00:03:31,800
This is a rare chance to learn.

62
00:03:32,120 --> 00:03:33,640
Can't you handle this difficulty?

63
00:03:33,640 --> 00:03:34,880
I can.

64
00:03:35,200 --> 00:03:36,040
Come on, come on.

65
00:03:36,806 --> 00:03:37,960
- Hang in there.
- Come here.

66
00:03:37,960 --> 00:03:39,360
- Hang in there.
- Go.

67
00:03:39,360 --> 00:03:40,366
Overcome this difficulty.

68
00:03:40,840 --> 00:03:42,040
Hold that rope up.

69
00:03:42,520 --> 00:03:43,360
Yes, pull it tight.

70
00:03:43,360 --> 00:03:44,420
Pull it dead tight.

71
00:03:44,440 --> 00:03:46,150
The moment that tests us has arrived.

72
00:03:46,210 --> 00:03:47,680
- Get ready to move.
- Hang in there.

73
00:03:47,680 --> 00:03:49,280
We must overcome this difficulty.

74
00:03:49,880 --> 00:03:51,720
Don't leave. Sit down.

75
00:03:53,034 --> 00:03:54,744
- Pull it tight.
- Peng Batian is leading

76
00:03:54,755 --> 00:03:56,505
- Pull it flat.
- the Baiji Society,

77
00:03:56,516 --> 00:03:57,420
killing along the way.

78
00:03:57,420 --> 00:03:58,733
They've reached the cross ferry.

79
00:03:59,160 --> 00:04:00,240
Great.

80
00:04:00,770 --> 00:04:02,890
♪The foes swim right into the net♪

81
00:04:06,030 --> 00:04:10,940
♪Wild winds can't bring down the sun♪

82
00:04:11,033 --> 00:04:12,560
- What are you doing?
- Why come back?

83
00:04:12,560 --> 00:04:13,800
- Go pull it.
- Hold it on.

84
00:04:13,800 --> 00:04:15,640
- Go.
- Go pull it, Hu Sanyuan.

85
00:04:15,640 --> 00:04:17,006
- Come here.
- What are you doing?

86
00:04:17,280 --> 00:04:18,880
- Go, go!
- Go pull it.

87
00:04:18,880 --> 00:04:23,290
♪Everyone joins the fight♪

88
00:04:23,290 --> 00:04:25,130
♪We'll drive all the foes away♪

89
00:04:25,130 --> 00:04:29,070
♪Drive them away♪

90
00:04:40,960 --> 00:04:42,320
Why did you sneak back like this?

91
00:04:43,280 --> 00:04:44,280
You didn't even tell me.

92
00:04:45,040 --> 00:04:45,880
You came back alone?

93
00:04:49,160 --> 00:04:50,140
Oh, you're carrying one.

94
00:04:52,960 --> 00:04:54,040
It's pitch-black in here.

95
00:04:54,040 --> 00:04:55,100
Why not turn on the light?

96
00:04:55,560 --> 00:04:56,400
Don't move.

97
00:05:00,520 --> 00:05:02,360
I was already on the table.

98
00:05:03,440 --> 00:05:04,280
But I got down.

99
00:05:05,800 --> 00:05:07,200
Either way, it's a life.

100
00:05:08,000 --> 00:05:08,840
I'm keeping it.

101
00:05:10,800 --> 00:05:11,640
Right.

102
00:05:12,960 --> 00:05:13,800
That's right.

103
00:05:14,840 --> 00:05:15,960
I'll be the kid's uncle.

104
00:05:24,520 --> 00:05:26,800
There's something else
I need to get straight.

105
00:05:27,360 --> 00:05:29,600
Before you left,
you had Laidi bring me a letter.

106
00:05:29,920 --> 00:05:31,213
The child got soaked in the rain.

107
00:05:31,280 --> 00:05:33,013
The letter got drenched;
the words blurred.

108
00:05:33,640 --> 00:05:34,779
I've been thinking about it.

109
00:05:35,160 --> 00:05:36,440
What exactly did that letter say?

110
00:05:36,440 --> 00:05:37,593
Were there any instructions?

111
00:05:38,040 --> 00:05:39,100
It doesn't matter anymore.

112
00:05:45,720 --> 00:05:46,880
We're putting on this opera.

113
00:05:47,360 --> 00:05:48,360
Hong Hu Chi Wei Dui.

114
00:05:48,840 --> 00:05:50,720
The film is for us to study.

115
00:05:51,360 --> 00:05:52,960
We're about to start rehearsals.

116
00:05:53,680 --> 00:05:54,920
Mi Lan is playing Han Ying.

117
00:06:06,280 --> 00:06:07,440
A great film.

118
00:06:08,480 --> 00:06:10,160
Good lines and songs.

119
00:06:10,160 --> 00:06:11,880
Such a pity. If only it were you.

120
00:06:34,360 --> 00:06:35,960
At the meeting early this morning,

121
00:06:35,960 --> 00:06:38,520
we were instructed repeatedly

122
00:06:38,520 --> 00:06:40,680
to act with caution.

123
00:06:40,680 --> 00:06:44,320
Do not make any rash moves.

124
00:06:45,080 --> 00:06:48,320
Do not make any rash moves.

125
00:06:54,960 --> 00:06:57,360
Captain, Captain.

126
00:06:57,360 --> 00:06:59,000
Secretary Han went to an early meeting.

127
00:06:59,000 --> 00:07:01,193
Captain, Peng Batian is leading

128
00:07:01,204 --> 00:07:02,880
the Baiji Society,
killing along the way.

129
00:07:02,880 --> 00:07:05,200
They've reached the cross ferry.

130
00:07:05,200 --> 00:07:13,160
♪Honghu waters, wave upon wave♪

131
00:07:13,400 --> 00:07:22,280
♪The shores of Honghu are my home♪

132
00:07:22,280 --> 00:07:26,960
♪Boats set out at dawn
to cast their nets♪

133
00:07:26,960 --> 00:07:31,920
♪Returning in the evening
with holds full of fish♪

134
00:07:32,200 --> 00:07:44,840
♪Returning in the evening
with holds full of fish♪

135
00:07:53,020 --> 00:07:56,700
(Music score of Hong Hu Chi Wei Dui)

136
00:07:56,720 --> 00:07:59,560
Let's do this line again.

137
00:08:00,360 --> 00:08:08,360
♪Everyone says heaven is beautiful♪

138
00:08:08,360 --> 00:08:17,360
♪But how can it compare
to Honghu's rich land?♪

139
00:08:19,080 --> 00:08:21,280
Why did you stop? Keep going.

140
00:08:26,520 --> 00:08:31,400
♪Thirty years on the east bank♪

141
00:08:31,400 --> 00:08:35,080
♪Forty years on the west♪

142
00:08:36,600 --> 00:08:42,480
♪Honghu is ours once again♪

143
00:08:42,480 --> 00:08:43,640
What's wrong, Qiu?

144
00:08:44,640 --> 00:08:47,760
Things change.

145
00:08:47,760 --> 00:08:51,160
Peng Batian is back!

146
00:08:52,320 --> 00:08:53,320
What's gotten into you?

147
00:08:53,640 --> 00:08:54,600
He's lost it.

148
00:08:54,600 --> 00:08:55,440
Look.

149
00:08:55,846 --> 00:08:57,206
(Hong Hu Chi Wei Dui)
What's this?

150
00:08:57,400 --> 00:08:58,240
A script.

151
00:08:58,600 --> 00:09:01,480
Huang Zhengjing and Zhu just asked me

152
00:09:01,480 --> 00:09:02,720
to play the lead villain.

153
00:09:02,720 --> 00:09:05,160
I'm Peng Batian now.

154
00:09:05,960 --> 00:09:07,560
The troupe doesn't have villains now?

155
00:09:08,000 --> 00:09:08,960
I'm a villain.

156
00:09:08,960 --> 00:09:10,579
- You don't look the part.
- Hu Sanyuan!

157
00:09:11,080 --> 00:09:12,440
Come on, you answer to me now.

158
00:09:12,800 --> 00:09:13,640
What are you doing?

159
00:09:13,760 --> 00:09:14,680
Hong Hu Chi Wei Dui

160
00:09:14,680 --> 00:09:15,760
is a major production.

161
00:09:15,760 --> 00:09:17,080
I'm short on people.

162
00:09:17,640 --> 00:09:18,640
I needed more people,

163
00:09:18,640 --> 00:09:20,106
so Director Huang assigned you to me.

164
00:09:20,440 --> 00:09:21,440
Why am I assigned to you?

165
00:09:22,040 --> 00:09:23,720
Do you need drum cues for carrying

166
00:09:23,720 --> 00:09:24,840
some ragged prop onstage?

167
00:09:25,280 --> 00:09:27,080
What drum cues?

168
00:09:27,080 --> 00:09:28,320
Come help me with props.

169
00:09:29,760 --> 00:09:31,120
Say that first. Creative work, huh?

170
00:09:31,600 --> 00:09:32,440
Let's go.

171
00:09:34,320 --> 00:09:36,080
There are two more here. Take them too.

172
00:09:36,360 --> 00:09:38,360
Dozens to feed, with barely three hands.

173
00:09:38,360 --> 00:09:39,900
One's off to play the villain.

174
00:09:40,000 --> 00:09:41,160
Why don't you take all of us,

175
00:09:41,160 --> 00:09:43,040
so everyone can eat the air?

176
00:09:43,040 --> 00:09:44,520
Master Song, yelling at me won't help.

177
00:09:44,520 --> 00:09:46,320
Take it to Director Huang.

178
00:09:46,480 --> 00:09:47,640
I'm a brick of the revolution.

179
00:09:47,640 --> 00:09:49,160
I'm moved wherever I'm needed.

180
00:09:49,160 --> 00:09:50,720
On the Great Wall, I won't brag;

181
00:09:50,720 --> 00:09:53,000
in a latrine, I won't feel down.

182
00:09:53,560 --> 00:09:54,440
Master Song,

183
00:09:54,440 --> 00:09:55,800
there are scallions left.

184
00:09:55,800 --> 00:09:56,640
Chop, chop, chop.

185
00:09:56,920 --> 00:09:57,840
Hu Sanyuan,

186
00:09:58,200 --> 00:09:59,600
you're a traitor too.

187
00:09:59,600 --> 00:10:01,160
If you leave, who does the work?

188
00:10:01,380 --> 00:10:02,360
All right, that's enough.

189
00:10:02,360 --> 00:10:04,440
Opera comes first in the troupe.

190
00:10:04,920 --> 00:10:06,120
Come on, cook.

191
00:10:06,120 --> 00:10:07,600
Zip it and get back to work.

192
00:10:07,840 --> 00:10:08,813
You chop the scallions.

193
00:10:09,880 --> 00:10:12,960
For years, eight shows for everyone.

194
00:10:13,305 --> 00:10:15,039
Forget whether the audience
is sick of it.

195
00:10:15,050 --> 00:10:17,090
We're tired of acting it, right?

196
00:10:17,530 --> 00:10:18,440
So, this time,

197
00:10:18,440 --> 00:10:19,920
everyone in the troupe

198
00:10:20,240 --> 00:10:21,640
is like monkeys let loose

199
00:10:21,640 --> 00:10:23,400
for Hong Hu Chi Wei Dui.

200
00:10:23,400 --> 00:10:25,360
No one can stop us.

201
00:10:27,640 --> 00:10:28,640
Cut the warm-up.

202
00:10:28,640 --> 00:10:30,160
Just tell him what you want to make.

203
00:10:30,920 --> 00:10:31,760
Fine.

204
00:10:33,000 --> 00:10:33,840
Nail.

205
00:10:34,440 --> 00:10:36,680
Your chance to shine is here. Look.

206
00:10:37,280 --> 00:10:38,120
What is it?

207
00:10:40,760 --> 00:10:42,440
(Hong Hu Chi Wei Dui Prop List)
30 rifles.

208
00:10:42,440 --> 00:10:44,120
5 Mauser pistols.

209
00:10:44,600 --> 00:10:45,960
20 broadswords.

210
00:10:48,040 --> 00:10:49,713
A provincial Qinqiang Opera show

211
00:10:49,724 --> 00:10:51,120
wouldn't be any bigger than this.

212
00:10:51,120 --> 00:10:52,360
It's a rare chance.

213
00:10:53,040 --> 00:10:54,960
This time, we need to do it right

214
00:10:54,960 --> 00:10:56,120
and stage a major opera.

215
00:10:56,120 --> 00:10:57,560
Big ambitions.

216
00:10:59,120 --> 00:11:00,120
Well.

217
00:11:00,120 --> 00:11:01,920
With this much work, we can't keep up.

218
00:11:03,720 --> 00:11:05,400
You have help.

219
00:11:07,280 --> 00:11:08,120
Right.

220
00:11:08,160 --> 00:11:09,000
Hu Sanyuan.

221
00:11:09,400 --> 00:11:10,240
Here.

222
00:11:11,200 --> 00:11:12,440
You're prepping this, okay?

223
00:11:14,920 --> 00:11:15,920
I am?

224
00:11:17,080 --> 00:11:18,280
Props are all on you now.

225
00:11:18,920 --> 00:11:19,760
If so,

226
00:11:19,760 --> 00:11:20,640
what are you doing?

227
00:11:21,060 --> 00:11:23,510
I have sets and slides to draw

228
00:11:23,510 --> 00:11:24,400
and prisons and a home

229
00:11:24,400 --> 00:11:25,760
for Peng Batian to build.

230
00:11:25,760 --> 00:11:27,160
I've got plenty on my plate.

231
00:11:30,000 --> 00:11:31,320
It's a ton of work.

232
00:11:31,320 --> 00:11:32,400
I can't handle it alone.

233
00:11:33,050 --> 00:11:33,920
I can't do it.

234
00:11:33,920 --> 00:11:35,280
If you can't, tell Director Huang.

235
00:11:35,580 --> 00:11:36,440
You little brat,

236
00:11:36,440 --> 00:11:38,240
using Huang Zhengjing to pressure me?

237
00:11:38,240 --> 00:11:39,120
Director, look. Look!

238
00:11:40,280 --> 00:11:41,120
Hu Sanyuan,

239
00:11:41,320 --> 00:11:44,120
it was I who told Huang Zhengjing
to put you on props.

240
00:11:44,120 --> 00:11:45,440
You're too outstanding

241
00:11:45,440 --> 00:11:46,520
to work in the kitchen.

242
00:11:46,520 --> 00:11:47,680
That's a great injustice.

243
00:11:48,100 --> 00:11:49,000
I don't think so.

244
00:11:49,000 --> 00:11:50,000
It's not an injustice.

245
00:11:50,320 --> 00:11:52,000
The kitchen food is pretty good anyway.

246
00:11:52,000 --> 00:11:54,320
Why should I come here to be treated

247
00:11:54,320 --> 00:11:55,200
like donkeys?

248
00:11:55,920 --> 00:11:56,760
Listen to me.

249
00:11:57,200 --> 00:11:58,960
Besides you,

250
00:11:58,960 --> 00:12:01,280
no one in the troupe can handle this.

251
00:12:01,800 --> 00:12:03,840
Don't flatter me. It's no use.

252
00:12:05,040 --> 00:12:06,360
Anyway, this is settled.

253
00:12:06,640 --> 00:12:08,000
I'm just here to inform you.

254
00:12:09,240 --> 00:12:11,480
Look how great you think you are.
Just putting on a play.

255
00:12:12,513 --> 00:12:13,520
Why don't you get a cannon

256
00:12:13,520 --> 00:12:15,240
and blow up Peng Batian's house?

257
00:12:23,720 --> 00:12:24,560
Mi Lan,

258
00:12:24,600 --> 00:12:26,360
you sang the "Honghu waters" section

259
00:12:26,640 --> 00:12:28,320
so beautifully.

260
00:12:29,440 --> 00:12:30,480
This part

261
00:12:30,480 --> 00:12:32,200
was transplanted from the opera,

262
00:12:32,200 --> 00:12:33,920
and the adaptation is very successful.

263
00:12:34,120 --> 00:12:36,560
The melody is lovely;
it rolls off the tongue.

264
00:12:36,560 --> 00:12:37,606
Anyone would sing it well.

265
00:12:38,040 --> 00:12:38,880
That's not true.

266
00:12:39,200 --> 00:12:40,320
Once you perform this play,

267
00:12:40,320 --> 00:12:41,840
it's sure to be a success.

268
00:12:41,840 --> 00:12:42,900
Exactly, exactly.

269
00:12:42,900 --> 00:12:44,966
Once you perform it,
this play is sure to be a hit.

270
00:12:46,080 --> 00:12:47,680
It's everyone pulling together.

271
00:12:47,680 --> 00:12:48,600
If the play succeeds,

272
00:12:48,600 --> 00:12:49,920
the credit will be everyone's.

273
00:12:50,480 --> 00:12:51,680
We're all supporting roles.

274
00:12:51,680 --> 00:12:53,360
You, however, are the lead.

275
00:12:54,920 --> 00:12:56,360
Ms. Hua, you're washing up too.

276
00:12:56,360 --> 00:12:58,160
The audience mainly comes
to see the star.

277
00:12:58,160 --> 00:12:59,080
You're washing up too.

278
00:13:00,400 --> 00:13:01,240
You go ahead.

279
00:13:01,240 --> 00:13:02,640
I'm done. I'm heading back first.

280
00:13:02,640 --> 00:13:03,480
All right.

281
00:13:06,000 --> 00:13:06,960
Too cold.

282
00:13:09,960 --> 00:13:11,800
I'm heading back too. Too cold.

283
00:13:19,440 --> 00:13:20,920
I watched you rehearse today.

284
00:13:21,400 --> 00:13:22,240
It was quite good.

285
00:13:23,120 --> 00:13:23,960
Thank you.

286
00:13:27,200 --> 00:13:29,200
The "Honghu waters" section

287
00:13:29,560 --> 00:13:30,760
is very soft and graceful.

288
00:13:30,760 --> 00:13:32,200
You could sing it with more boldness.

289
00:13:37,440 --> 00:13:38,360
I think

290
00:13:38,920 --> 00:13:41,240
that Han Ying is a hero,

291
00:13:41,240 --> 00:13:42,600
but she's also a woman.

292
00:13:43,080 --> 00:13:44,800
The whole play is full of boldness,

293
00:13:44,800 --> 00:13:45,800
but

294
00:13:46,560 --> 00:13:48,760
this is the tender, emotional section.

295
00:13:48,760 --> 00:13:50,920
Shouldn't it show her feminine side?

296
00:13:52,440 --> 00:13:53,600
That's different.

297
00:13:54,360 --> 00:13:55,920
She is no ordinary woman.

298
00:13:55,920 --> 00:13:57,720
She is the soul of the team.

299
00:13:57,720 --> 00:13:59,440
The moment she opens her voice,

300
00:13:59,440 --> 00:14:02,240
you have to feel
she's the pillar of the troupe.

301
00:14:05,480 --> 00:14:06,320
Ms. Hua,

302
00:14:07,720 --> 00:14:08,960
we are not the same person.

303
00:14:09,400 --> 00:14:11,480
Shouldn't we sing different Han Yings?

304
00:14:14,520 --> 00:14:15,360
Yes.

305
00:14:16,640 --> 00:14:17,480
I spoke out of turn.

306
00:14:26,120 --> 00:14:26,960
Caixiang,

307
00:14:28,520 --> 00:14:29,360
thank you.

308
00:14:32,160 --> 00:14:33,000
It's nothing.

309
00:15:03,960 --> 00:15:04,800
Hu Sanyuan,

310
00:15:04,960 --> 00:15:06,560
where on earth are you taking me?

311
00:15:07,480 --> 00:15:09,200
Just take your ride.

312
00:15:10,080 --> 00:15:12,680
Today, the seven-character quatrain
we are learning

313
00:15:12,760 --> 00:15:13,840
is Cun Ju.

314
00:15:13,840 --> 00:15:17,760
The first two lines describe the scene;
the last two describe the people.

315
00:15:17,760 --> 00:15:20,960
Among them, what technique is used
with "brush" and "drunk"?

316
00:15:20,960 --> 00:15:23,160
Personification.

317
00:15:25,120 --> 00:15:26,640
This is Nail; you've met him.

318
00:15:27,280 --> 00:15:29,160
This is the Qiaolian I told you about.

319
00:15:29,800 --> 00:15:30,680
Hello, Qiaolian.

320
00:15:30,680 --> 00:15:31,520
Hello.

321
00:15:31,680 --> 00:15:33,800
Qiaolian, two things today.

322
00:15:34,440 --> 00:15:35,600
First,

323
00:15:35,800 --> 00:15:36,880
to introduce you two.

324
00:15:38,040 --> 00:15:38,960
Second,

325
00:15:38,960 --> 00:15:40,020
I need to ask you a favor.

326
00:15:40,373 --> 00:15:41,280
Start with the second.

327
00:15:42,200 --> 00:15:43,560
The troupe is staging a play.

328
00:15:44,286 --> 00:15:45,633
We need some red-tasseled spears.

329
00:15:46,120 --> 00:15:47,720
Could we borrow your students'

330
00:15:47,720 --> 00:15:48,760
red-tasseled spears?

331
00:15:49,440 --> 00:15:50,920
If you do the troupe a favor,

332
00:15:51,200 --> 00:15:52,920
let's call it mutual help.

333
00:15:53,040 --> 00:15:53,880
Right?

334
00:15:54,640 --> 00:15:55,480
How many do you need?

335
00:15:55,840 --> 00:15:56,920
Forty.

336
00:15:56,920 --> 00:15:57,760
That many?

337
00:16:00,640 --> 00:16:03,440
Well, I'll go report it
to the school leadership.

338
00:16:03,440 --> 00:16:04,760
For our County Troupe,

339
00:16:05,240 --> 00:16:06,320
it should be no problem.

340
00:16:07,000 --> 00:16:08,360
All right, make it quick.

341
00:16:09,720 --> 00:16:11,040
Your leg has healed, hasn't it?

342
00:16:11,440 --> 00:16:13,320
Nail cares about you a lot.

343
00:16:13,320 --> 00:16:14,640
It's healed, no problem.

344
00:16:15,240 --> 00:16:16,080
Don't you limp?

345
00:16:16,160 --> 00:16:17,220
Who said I limp?

346
00:16:17,231 --> 00:16:18,280
How could I possibly limp?

347
00:16:18,280 --> 00:16:19,920
What nonsense are you talking about?

348
00:16:20,560 --> 00:16:22,760
See? Now you're relieved.

349
00:16:23,320 --> 00:16:24,960
What's there for me
to be relieved about?

350
00:16:25,520 --> 00:16:26,960
You two have now officially met.

351
00:16:26,960 --> 00:16:28,320
Chat a while on your own.

352
00:16:29,080 --> 00:16:30,233
I'm off to browse the street.

353
00:16:35,960 --> 00:16:36,800
Hello.

354
00:16:36,920 --> 00:16:37,800
Sit, sit.

355
00:16:38,400 --> 00:16:39,360
Sit, sit.

356
00:16:39,360 --> 00:16:40,840
Come on, don't stand on ceremony.

357
00:16:41,440 --> 00:16:42,280
Then I'll sit.

358
00:16:45,560 --> 00:16:46,400
Sit here.

359
00:16:46,720 --> 00:16:47,560
Okay.

360
00:16:51,720 --> 00:16:52,560
No pushing!

361
00:16:56,480 --> 00:16:57,760
Forget it, let's go.

362
00:17:02,200 --> 00:17:03,040
Sit down.

363
00:17:03,160 --> 00:17:04,840
- Sure.
- How old are you?

364
00:17:05,760 --> 00:17:07,040
Well... 28.

365
00:17:09,200 --> 00:17:10,480
Push. Don't slack off.

366
00:17:17,640 --> 00:17:19,520
On the way here,
you let me ride the cart.

367
00:17:20,220 --> 00:17:21,940
On the way back,
you won't even let me sit.

368
00:17:22,080 --> 00:17:23,520
On the way here, it was downhill,

369
00:17:23,920 --> 00:17:25,360
so I let you be comfortable.

370
00:17:25,371 --> 00:17:26,513
On the way back, it's uphill,

371
00:17:26,524 --> 00:17:27,844
and you still want to laze around?

372
00:17:29,160 --> 00:17:30,280
Why don't you say

373
00:17:30,666 --> 00:17:32,520
that there were two bachelors
on the way here,

374
00:17:32,520 --> 00:17:34,393
and there's only one bachelor
on the way back?

375
00:17:35,160 --> 00:17:36,400
You've got what you want.

376
00:17:37,480 --> 00:17:39,600
You've successfully dumped
the burden on me.

377
00:17:39,860 --> 00:17:41,593
I'd like to take on a burden
like that too.

378
00:17:41,720 --> 00:17:42,760
Who'll dump one on me?

379
00:17:53,600 --> 00:17:54,440
I'm coming in.

380
00:17:59,560 --> 00:18:00,600
I went to the countryside

381
00:18:01,080 --> 00:18:02,080
and got you some eggs.

382
00:18:02,560 --> 00:18:03,400
You jerk.

383
00:18:04,760 --> 00:18:05,920
Barred Rock eggs.

384
00:18:06,360 --> 00:18:07,200
Take them away.

385
00:18:07,360 --> 00:18:08,200
I don't want them.

386
00:18:11,600 --> 00:18:13,080
Don't fight against yourself.

387
00:18:14,000 --> 00:18:15,600
If fate has decided it,

388
00:18:15,600 --> 00:18:16,640
just accept it openly.

389
00:18:18,200 --> 00:18:19,280
I shouldn't have come back.

390
00:18:20,360 --> 00:18:21,473
Completely superfluous here.

391
00:18:30,440 --> 00:18:31,280
Stop right there.

392
00:18:33,800 --> 00:18:34,640
Take them away.

393
00:18:35,320 --> 00:18:36,720
What are you doing?

394
00:18:38,320 --> 00:18:40,160
Comrades should care for each other.

395
00:18:40,160 --> 00:18:41,040
I've decided.

396
00:18:42,880 --> 00:18:43,720
Decided what?

397
00:18:43,720 --> 00:18:44,560
To transfer out.

398
00:18:45,153 --> 00:18:46,553
I'll go to Zhang Guangrong's place.

399
00:18:47,320 --> 00:18:48,253
No more opera singing?

400
00:18:49,240 --> 00:18:50,080
No more.

401
00:18:51,480 --> 00:18:52,320
I don't agree.

402
00:18:52,560 --> 00:18:54,040
My drumsticks don't agree either.

403
00:18:54,040 --> 00:18:56,040
What difference does it make
if you agree or not?

404
00:19:00,080 --> 00:19:02,440
This is your old nest,
your headquarters,

405
00:19:02,440 --> 00:19:03,320
and your base.

406
00:19:04,280 --> 00:19:05,160
It was before.

407
00:19:06,280 --> 00:19:07,280
Not anymore.

408
00:19:08,920 --> 00:19:10,000
I'm just an outsider now.

409
00:19:11,960 --> 00:19:13,760
That's only true
if you stop singing opera.

410
00:19:15,080 --> 00:19:16,000
Who are you?

411
00:19:16,440 --> 00:19:17,960
It's none of your business.

412
00:19:17,960 --> 00:19:19,960
What's my situation to you?

413
00:19:22,035 --> 00:19:23,502
Why are they arguing? What happened?

414
00:19:23,513 --> 00:19:24,353
No idea.

415
00:19:24,760 --> 00:19:25,680
Hu Sanyuan.

416
00:19:27,480 --> 00:19:28,320
Come here.

417
00:19:33,640 --> 00:19:35,120
Easy, easy.

418
00:19:47,680 --> 00:19:48,600
What is this thing?

419
00:19:49,480 --> 00:19:50,640
A homemade cannon.

420
00:19:52,520 --> 00:19:53,880
I've thought it over.

421
00:19:54,320 --> 00:19:55,760
Your idea was good.

422
00:19:55,760 --> 00:19:57,880
You've got guts and bold ideas.

423
00:19:58,280 --> 00:20:00,320
I've decided to take your suggestion.

424
00:20:00,320 --> 00:20:01,960
At the very end of the play,

425
00:20:02,206 --> 00:20:03,320
we'll use a homemade cannon

426
00:20:03,320 --> 00:20:05,360
to bring down
Peng Batian's courtyard wall

427
00:20:05,560 --> 00:20:06,520
and kill Peng Batian.

428
00:20:08,200 --> 00:20:09,360
Are you serious?

429
00:20:09,360 --> 00:20:10,280
Of course.

430
00:20:11,360 --> 00:20:12,960
I was just talking nonsense.

431
00:20:13,200 --> 00:20:14,880
Your nonsense was brilliant.

432
00:20:14,880 --> 00:20:16,520
Listen, I've never found

433
00:20:16,520 --> 00:20:19,040
a breakthrough for this play.

434
00:20:19,440 --> 00:20:20,600
Now, I have.

435
00:20:20,600 --> 00:20:21,800
Blowing up Peng Batian

436
00:20:21,800 --> 00:20:23,240
is the perfect breakthrough.

437
00:20:23,760 --> 00:20:25,560
The audience will find it satisfying.

438
00:20:25,840 --> 00:20:26,680
Our play

439
00:20:26,680 --> 00:20:28,160
will surely be a huge success.

440
00:20:28,600 --> 00:20:29,640
So, it's settled.

441
00:20:30,160 --> 00:20:31,600
Settled for what?

442
00:20:31,600 --> 00:20:33,040
I don't know how to make this cannon.

443
00:20:35,360 --> 00:20:36,200
Hu Sanyuan,

444
00:20:36,640 --> 00:20:38,200
I've been a director for half my life.

445
00:20:38,200 --> 00:20:39,600
I'm about to retire.

446
00:20:40,200 --> 00:20:41,160
This might well be

447
00:20:41,160 --> 00:20:42,480
the last play I direct.

448
00:20:43,000 --> 00:20:44,680
I also want to put a perfect full stop

449
00:20:44,680 --> 00:20:46,440
on my directing career.

450
00:20:47,160 --> 00:20:48,680
Just do me this favor, all right?

451
00:20:50,040 --> 00:20:51,040
I'll give you a bow.

452
00:20:57,720 --> 00:20:58,560
I'm begging you.

453
00:21:02,920 --> 00:21:04,240
Our goal is

454
00:21:04,240 --> 00:21:06,680
to make achievements
in agriculture, industry,

455
00:21:06,680 --> 00:21:08,440
national defense,
and science and technology

456
00:21:08,440 --> 00:21:09,960
within this century.

457
00:21:28,080 --> 00:21:28,920
Qin Feng.

458
00:21:32,600 --> 00:21:33,440
What are you doing?

459
00:21:39,600 --> 00:21:40,953
Why are you making a homemade gun?

460
00:21:42,360 --> 00:21:44,280
Si was stabbed to death
by people from Xiguan.

461
00:21:46,000 --> 00:21:47,000
When did this happen?

462
00:21:47,680 --> 00:21:48,520
A couple of days ago.

463
00:21:53,320 --> 00:21:54,280
What do you need?

464
00:21:55,800 --> 00:21:57,760
I want to ask you
to help me make something.

465
00:22:07,979 --> 00:22:09,206
Who are you planning to blast?

466
00:22:25,520 --> 00:22:26,440
Let me see.

467
00:22:38,840 --> 00:22:39,720
This is powerful.

468
00:22:45,840 --> 00:22:46,880
What are you doing?

469
00:22:46,880 --> 00:22:47,720
Are you crazy?

470
00:22:47,720 --> 00:22:49,880
You're too old for this!

471
00:22:50,560 --> 00:22:51,880
Impulsive when young is one thing.

472
00:22:51,880 --> 00:22:53,440
Now, you have a family.

473
00:22:53,440 --> 00:22:55,040
Aren't you stupid to do this?

474
00:22:55,480 --> 00:22:57,280
Who do you think you are, lecturing me?

475
00:22:57,960 --> 00:22:58,880
You were tough before;

476
00:22:58,880 --> 00:23:00,160
now, you're just a fool.

477
00:23:00,320 --> 00:23:02,040
Making homemade guns is illegal.

478
00:23:02,040 --> 00:23:03,080
You'll go to prison.

479
00:23:03,080 --> 00:23:04,520
You have a family.

480
00:23:04,640 --> 00:23:05,920
If something happens to you,

481
00:23:05,920 --> 00:23:07,120
what will they do?

482
00:23:07,520 --> 00:23:08,600
Si is dead!

483
00:23:09,120 --> 00:23:10,600
Even so, you can't commit a crime.

484
00:23:10,720 --> 00:23:12,073
Try it again, and I'll report you.

485
00:23:16,240 --> 00:23:23,520
♪Only hatred fills my chest♪

486
00:23:26,160 --> 00:23:28,960
♪Let the enemy rage as they may♪

487
00:23:28,960 --> 00:23:31,520
♪The setting sun won't last long♪

488
00:23:35,640 --> 00:23:46,200
♪Through a mountain of swords
and a sea of fire♪

489
00:23:49,920 --> 00:23:51,120
Stop, stop.

490
00:23:51,120 --> 00:23:51,960
Hold it.

491
00:23:53,200 --> 00:23:54,320
What's going on, Mi Lan?

492
00:23:54,320 --> 00:23:55,720
Why couldn't you hit the note again?

493
00:23:56,022 --> 00:23:57,229
We've been rehearsing all day.

494
00:23:57,240 --> 00:23:58,800
Why do you fail to do it every time?

495
00:23:59,280 --> 00:24:00,560
At this point in the play,

496
00:24:00,560 --> 00:24:02,560
your emotion
should be getting more intense.

497
00:24:02,560 --> 00:24:03,840
Why is there no passion at all?

498
00:24:04,120 --> 00:24:04,960
Director,

499
00:24:05,520 --> 00:24:07,280
this part should come in
on the beat now.

500
00:24:07,760 --> 00:24:09,000
The rhythm should kick in.

501
00:24:09,400 --> 00:24:11,400
If the drums lack power,
how can I have passion?

502
00:24:11,400 --> 00:24:13,120
Even if I shred my voice, it's useless.

503
00:24:14,160 --> 00:24:15,440
How is this our fault suddenly?

504
00:24:16,433 --> 00:24:17,713
How are we not giving it power?

505
00:24:17,724 --> 00:24:18,960
The drum is nearly smashed.

506
00:24:18,960 --> 00:24:20,520
What more can we do?

507
00:24:20,520 --> 00:24:21,720
Mr. He,

508
00:24:21,720 --> 00:24:23,720
one beat, one clap.

509
00:24:23,720 --> 00:24:24,840
You're not giving it power.

510
00:24:24,840 --> 00:24:26,560
At this point,
if the rhythm can't keep up,

511
00:24:26,800 --> 00:24:28,120
my singing won't change a thing.

512
00:24:28,120 --> 00:24:30,320
What's wrong with you?

513
00:24:30,600 --> 00:24:31,840
The tempo wasn't slow at all.

514
00:24:32,160 --> 00:24:33,360
Unbelievable.

515
00:24:33,360 --> 00:24:35,400
You were just off-tune and off-beat,
you know?

516
00:24:35,540 --> 00:24:36,890
What do you mean?

517
00:24:37,080 --> 00:24:38,091
When Hu Sanyuan plays,

518
00:24:38,102 --> 00:24:39,418
he watches the actress's rhythm.

519
00:24:39,429 --> 00:24:40,705
You just bury your head in it.

520
00:24:40,716 --> 00:24:42,262
Your drumsticks even fell to the floor.

521
00:24:42,273 --> 00:24:43,120
How can you blame me?

522
00:24:43,120 --> 00:24:44,320
Why don't you let him play it?

523
00:24:44,320 --> 00:24:45,640
Let's see who has the problem.

524
00:24:45,640 --> 00:24:46,760
Your eyes are so sharp

525
00:24:46,760 --> 00:24:48,280
that you can see my drumsticks fall.

526
00:24:48,280 --> 00:24:49,160
Hu Sanyuan?

527
00:24:49,440 --> 00:24:51,160
Why don't you ask Hua Caixiang to sing?

528
00:24:51,160 --> 00:24:52,080
Stop arguing.

529
00:24:53,000 --> 00:24:55,360
Hu Sanyuan, Hu Sanyuan.

530
00:24:56,570 --> 00:24:57,500
Come here.

531
00:24:57,520 --> 00:24:58,560
Here, over here.

532
00:25:00,560 --> 00:25:01,400
What?

533
00:25:01,880 --> 00:25:03,000
Play this section.

534
00:25:04,280 --> 00:25:05,120
I can't do it.

535
00:25:06,000 --> 00:25:06,840
Why not?

536
00:25:07,400 --> 00:25:08,280
I only have two hands.

537
00:25:08,560 --> 00:25:10,340
I'm not saying
I don't watch the actress.

538
00:25:10,480 --> 00:25:12,930
What's so great
about watching actresses?

539
00:25:13,120 --> 00:25:14,160
We're the drummers.

540
00:25:14,160 --> 00:25:15,520
Why should we watch the actresses?

541
00:25:15,520 --> 00:25:17,030
- Mr. He.
- What?

542
00:25:17,030 --> 00:25:19,560
Shouldn't the drumming follow
the actress's rhythm?

543
00:25:20,080 --> 00:25:21,120
And there you are,

544
00:25:21,120 --> 00:25:22,173
blindly drumming away.

545
00:25:22,184 --> 00:25:23,735
- What can I do?
- We keep the rhythm.

546
00:25:23,746 --> 00:25:25,080
We're not here to watch the show.

547
00:25:25,080 --> 00:25:26,520
Can this play still go on?

548
00:25:26,840 --> 00:25:28,200
If not, let's just break up.

549
00:25:28,200 --> 00:25:29,680
Don't ruin such a good play.

550
00:25:30,720 --> 00:25:32,160
The orchestra and the vocals

551
00:25:32,160 --> 00:25:33,760
have always been intertwined,

552
00:25:34,120 --> 00:25:36,160
helping each other.

553
00:25:36,600 --> 00:25:38,720
Yet you two keep blaming each other.

554
00:25:39,280 --> 00:25:41,240
It'd be a miracle
if the play didn't fall apart.

555
00:25:44,080 --> 00:25:45,250
Come on, let's play.

556
00:25:45,550 --> 00:25:47,060
Put some power into it.

557
00:25:51,320 --> 00:25:52,800
You drew this?

558
00:25:53,600 --> 00:25:55,320
I drew all of these. Look.

559
00:25:55,720 --> 00:25:56,560
This.

560
00:25:57,280 --> 00:25:58,440
This one, and this one.

561
00:25:58,440 --> 00:25:59,360
I drew all of them.

562
00:25:59,600 --> 00:26:00,440
How is it?

563
00:26:01,240 --> 00:26:02,080
- Good.
- Have some.

564
00:26:02,080 --> 00:26:03,800
Have some peanuts. And this too.

565
00:26:04,680 --> 00:26:06,040
I designed all these blueprints.

566
00:26:08,120 --> 00:26:08,960
How about that?

567
00:26:10,280 --> 00:26:12,520
Listen, not just these blueprints.

568
00:26:12,520 --> 00:26:13,760
Look over there, the backdrops.

569
00:26:14,640 --> 00:26:15,480
Look.

570
00:26:15,760 --> 00:26:16,600
These.

571
00:26:16,860 --> 00:26:18,120
These scenery flats at the back.

572
00:26:18,120 --> 00:26:19,120
I painted all of them.

573
00:26:19,120 --> 00:26:19,960
And I used this.

574
00:26:21,080 --> 00:26:22,120
Can I touch it?

575
00:26:22,120 --> 00:26:23,360
Sure, go right ahead.

576
00:26:32,800 --> 00:26:34,200
This is where I usually live.

577
00:26:36,760 --> 00:26:39,000
Usually, no one helps tidy up here.

578
00:26:39,240 --> 00:26:40,080
It's a bit messy.

579
00:26:40,766 --> 00:26:41,920
Let me show you this. Come.

580
00:26:45,090 --> 00:26:46,570
This is the prison wall.

581
00:26:46,570 --> 00:26:47,420
You know?

582
00:26:47,520 --> 00:26:49,160
I painted all of it back there.

583
00:26:51,000 --> 00:26:51,840
Qiaolian.

584
00:26:52,760 --> 00:26:53,600
How was it today?

585
00:26:54,360 --> 00:26:55,680
Was the troupe interesting?

586
00:26:56,200 --> 00:26:58,120
I'd only watched performances before

587
00:26:58,120 --> 00:26:59,760
and never seen rehearsals.

588
00:27:00,520 --> 00:27:01,400
It was interesting.

589
00:27:01,400 --> 00:27:02,320
Listen to you.

590
00:27:02,960 --> 00:27:04,400
How could we

591
00:27:04,400 --> 00:27:06,193
casually let outsiders
watch the rehearsals?

592
00:27:07,000 --> 00:27:08,960
Today, you enjoyed family treatment.

593
00:27:08,960 --> 00:27:09,800
You know?

594
00:27:12,600 --> 00:27:14,240
I told you about letting you

595
00:27:14,240 --> 00:27:16,760
watch performances for free for life.
How about that?

596
00:27:17,080 --> 00:27:18,280
I kept my word, didn't I?

597
00:27:19,880 --> 00:27:21,520
Is your cannon ready yet?

598
00:27:22,040 --> 00:27:23,040
Almost.

599
00:27:23,360 --> 00:27:24,280
Will it go off?

600
00:27:24,600 --> 00:27:25,960
If not, can it be called a cannon?

601
00:27:27,640 --> 00:27:28,480
I'm telling you.

602
00:27:28,960 --> 00:27:30,240
Safety first.

603
00:27:30,240 --> 00:27:31,560
Don't you dare act crazy with me.

604
00:27:32,760 --> 00:27:34,360
Then what do you want me to do?

605
00:28:14,280 --> 00:28:15,120
How's that?

606
00:28:15,280 --> 00:28:16,160
Great.

607
00:28:20,120 --> 00:28:21,080
You're fine, huh?

608
00:28:48,440 --> 00:28:49,280
Hu Sanyuan,

609
00:28:50,080 --> 00:28:51,600
your cannon is short and thick.

610
00:28:52,040 --> 00:28:53,720
Can this stubby little thing work?

611
00:28:54,880 --> 00:28:55,760
Lie yourself down.

612
00:28:55,760 --> 00:28:57,360
See if you're as long as the barrel.

613
00:28:57,360 --> 00:28:58,560
What's with this idle chatter?

614
00:28:58,560 --> 00:28:59,720
Set one off for us to see.

615
00:29:11,320 --> 00:29:12,560
People up front, move aside.

616
00:29:13,720 --> 00:29:14,560
Nail.

617
00:29:14,840 --> 00:29:15,840
Get up on the platform.

618
00:29:16,360 --> 00:29:17,720
You're testing it on me?

619
00:29:17,720 --> 00:29:19,240
- Hurry up.
- You...

620
00:29:20,000 --> 00:29:20,920
Is it safe?

621
00:29:21,680 --> 00:29:22,560
Hu Sanyuan,

622
00:29:23,400 --> 00:29:24,520
don't mess around.

623
00:29:25,760 --> 00:29:26,840
Can you do it or not?

624
00:29:26,840 --> 00:29:28,080
There must not be any problems.

625
00:29:28,560 --> 00:29:30,240
Rest assured, everyone.

626
00:29:31,000 --> 00:29:32,680
This chicken has taken three blasts.

627
00:29:32,680 --> 00:29:33,926
It didn't lose a single feather.

628
00:29:35,720 --> 00:29:36,720
Come on.

629
00:29:37,520 --> 00:29:38,880
Everyone, stand back.

630
00:29:38,880 --> 00:29:40,040
Move aside.

631
00:29:40,040 --> 00:29:41,600
Come on, stand behind me.

632
00:29:42,280 --> 00:29:43,120
Nail.

633
00:29:43,280 --> 00:29:44,120
Light it.

634
00:29:44,840 --> 00:29:45,990
- Are you sure?
- Light it.

635
00:30:07,840 --> 00:30:08,840
(Best wishes)
Slow down.

636
00:30:09,999 --> 00:30:11,280
(to the premiere)
To the right.

637
00:30:11,280 --> 00:30:12,120
Yes, yes.

638
00:30:13,840 --> 00:30:15,440
(Revolutionary drama)
Take a look.

639
00:30:15,480 --> 00:30:16,579
(Hong Hu Chi Wei Dui)
Good.

640
00:30:20,800 --> 00:30:22,200
What are you pouting for?

641
00:30:22,840 --> 00:30:23,760
Hurry up and peel.

642
00:30:25,200 --> 00:30:26,960
Tonight is the official performance.

643
00:30:26,960 --> 00:30:28,200
We have to rehearse soon.

644
00:30:28,640 --> 00:30:30,593
You two
are just playing two lotus leaves,

645
00:30:30,604 --> 00:30:32,320
standing there motionless. Why rehearse?

646
00:30:32,320 --> 00:30:33,160
No need to go.

647
00:30:33,400 --> 00:30:34,720
We have to sway,

648
00:30:34,720 --> 00:30:36,200
like being blown by the wind.

649
00:30:36,720 --> 00:30:39,120
Even if you two sway into lotus fairies

650
00:30:39,120 --> 00:30:40,280
and lotus leaf sprites,

651
00:30:40,680 --> 00:30:42,120
you have to finish this first.

652
00:30:45,360 --> 00:30:46,440
You have to rehearse.

653
00:30:46,440 --> 00:30:47,640
Why did you run off here?

654
00:30:48,520 --> 00:30:49,760
They're peeling firecrackers.

655
00:30:49,760 --> 00:30:50,600
Get back.

656
00:30:52,160 --> 00:30:53,040
Mi Lan,

657
00:30:53,840 --> 00:30:55,880
your "Honghu waters" section

658
00:30:55,880 --> 00:30:57,160
is very soft and graceful,

659
00:30:58,200 --> 00:31:01,000
but if you added more heroic spirit,
it'd be even more perfect.

660
00:31:01,972 --> 00:31:03,133
She asked you to tell me that?

661
00:31:03,560 --> 00:31:04,440
Who?

662
00:31:04,440 --> 00:31:05,280
Hua Caixiang.

663
00:31:05,560 --> 00:31:06,800
What's it got to do with her?

664
00:31:07,160 --> 00:31:08,360
I think so myself.

665
00:31:10,800 --> 00:31:12,320
What else do you think I need

666
00:31:12,320 --> 00:31:13,240
to pay attention to?

667
00:31:13,920 --> 00:31:15,160
Be more confident.

668
00:31:15,720 --> 00:31:16,800
Tonight,

669
00:31:16,960 --> 00:31:18,360
it will surely be a huge success.

670
00:31:19,440 --> 00:31:20,280
Thank you.

671
00:31:28,820 --> 00:31:29,800
I haven't been paid yet.

672
00:31:29,800 --> 00:31:31,480
Next time, next time.

673
00:31:32,360 --> 00:31:33,880
They're here, Director.

674
00:31:33,880 --> 00:31:35,080
- They're here.
- Greet them.

675
00:31:35,080 --> 00:31:35,960
Let's go.

676
00:31:35,960 --> 00:31:37,080
- Make way.
- Clear the way.

677
00:31:37,080 --> 00:31:38,800
- Make way.
- Get in line.

678
00:31:38,800 --> 00:31:40,160
(Best wishes)
Line up.

679
00:31:41,400 --> 00:31:42,440
Welcome, welcome.

680
00:31:42,440 --> 00:31:43,320
- Good.
- Come.

681
00:31:43,320 --> 00:31:44,160
Maintain order.

682
00:31:44,160 --> 00:31:45,000
Hi, sir.

683
00:31:45,520 --> 00:31:46,360
Come, come.

684
00:31:46,360 --> 00:31:48,220
(Best wishes to the premiere)

685
00:31:49,200 --> 00:31:50,040
Come, come.

686
00:31:55,280 --> 00:31:56,600
Good, everyone, be alert.

687
00:31:56,600 --> 00:31:57,440
Good.

688
00:31:58,730 --> 00:31:59,980
- You're here.
- Are you ready?

689
00:31:59,980 --> 00:32:00,890
Yes.

690
00:32:02,826 --> 00:32:04,000
The leaders have all arrived.

691
00:32:04,600 --> 00:32:05,960
There must not be any trouble.

692
00:32:05,960 --> 00:32:07,320
Don't worry, no problem.

693
00:32:10,240 --> 00:32:11,080
Secretary,

694
00:32:11,193 --> 00:32:12,160
from your busy schedule,

695
00:32:12,160 --> 00:32:13,520
thank you for coming to inspect.

696
00:32:13,520 --> 00:32:14,400
It's only right.

697
00:32:17,560 --> 00:32:18,440
It's time.

698
00:32:19,600 --> 00:32:20,440
Begin.

699
00:32:27,300 --> 00:32:32,460
(Best wishes to the premiere)

700
00:32:52,040 --> 00:32:52,880
Hu Sanyuan,

701
00:32:53,240 --> 00:32:54,120
how's it going?

702
00:32:54,520 --> 00:32:56,160
Everything is ready,
waiting for the cue.

703
00:32:56,510 --> 00:32:57,440
Let me tell you.

704
00:32:57,440 --> 00:32:59,280
The CRC leaders are all here.

705
00:32:59,280 --> 00:33:01,080
We must not drop the ball.

706
00:33:01,240 --> 00:33:02,680
Especially that final cannon blast.

707
00:33:02,680 --> 00:33:04,400
That's the most crucial part.

708
00:33:04,960 --> 00:33:06,920
This is no simple cannon blast;

709
00:33:06,920 --> 00:33:09,840
it's a continuation
of the October Revolution cannon fire.

710
00:33:09,840 --> 00:33:11,800
We must make it earth-shaking.

711
00:33:11,800 --> 00:33:13,360
Earth-shaking, understand?

712
00:33:13,360 --> 00:33:14,840
Relax, relax.

713
00:33:16,640 --> 00:33:17,960
I'm counting on you.

714
00:33:17,960 --> 00:33:18,920
I'll head over first.

715
00:33:21,560 --> 00:33:24,560
♪Honghu waters, long and long♪

716
00:33:24,720 --> 00:33:27,560
♪The people's hearts turn
toward the Party♪

717
00:33:27,640 --> 00:33:30,640
♪He Long led the revolution♪

718
00:33:30,760 --> 00:33:33,600
♪Red flags flutter, winning the battles♪

719
00:33:33,680 --> 00:33:36,680
♪Men held red-tasseled spears♪

720
00:33:36,760 --> 00:33:39,640
♪Women took up blades
to defend their homes♪

721
00:33:39,720 --> 00:33:42,760
♪Red Guard members
stepped forward bravely♪

722
00:33:42,800 --> 00:33:46,120
♪With shared hatred,
they headed to the battlefield♪

723
00:33:57,520 --> 00:33:59,200
Move out.

724
00:33:59,760 --> 00:34:00,680
Sure.

725
00:34:01,120 --> 00:34:05,520
Comrades, wait a moment.

726
00:34:20,200 --> 00:34:21,040
Deputy Director Zhu.

727
00:34:21,160 --> 00:34:22,000
Deputy Director Zhu,

728
00:34:22,040 --> 00:34:22,960
chaos outside the door.

729
00:34:23,880 --> 00:34:24,960
Our star performer.

730
00:34:25,600 --> 00:34:26,480
Not bad.

731
00:34:49,020 --> 00:34:52,220
(Qi Xi Bai Hu Tuan)

732
00:34:52,220 --> 00:34:54,260
(Sha Jia Bang)

733
00:34:55,820 --> 00:34:59,180
(Hong Deng Ji)

734
00:35:13,830 --> 00:35:15,870
If the Baiji Society
dares to set foot in Honghu...

735
00:35:16,000 --> 00:35:16,960
Leaders, leaders.

736
00:35:16,960 --> 00:35:18,230
- Director.
- They'll be smashed

737
00:35:18,230 --> 00:35:19,279
- Director.
- to pieces.

738
00:35:19,290 --> 00:35:20,270
- Director.
- Move out.

739
00:35:20,270 --> 00:35:21,160
The singing is not bad.

740
00:35:21,880 --> 00:35:23,040
Don't come any closer.

741
00:35:23,040 --> 00:35:24,720
Whoever breaks my gate down today

742
00:35:24,720 --> 00:35:25,560
will pay for it.

743
00:35:26,960 --> 00:35:27,840
No one can get in.

744
00:35:27,840 --> 00:35:28,680
You two, block them.

745
00:35:28,680 --> 00:35:29,840
What's all the shouting about?

746
00:35:30,440 --> 00:35:32,000
The leaders are watching the play.

747
00:35:32,000 --> 00:35:32,840
Director.

748
00:35:33,040 --> 00:35:34,000
What's going on?

749
00:35:34,540 --> 00:35:35,840
Too many people without tickets,

750
00:35:35,840 --> 00:35:37,059
clamoring to push their way in.

751
00:35:37,070 --> 00:35:38,909
Even the police
probably couldn't stop them.

752
00:35:38,920 --> 00:35:39,880
I'm telling you.

753
00:35:39,880 --> 00:35:42,120
The ones who came tonight
are all top county leaders.

754
00:35:42,120 --> 00:35:43,200
We can't lose control.

755
00:35:44,160 --> 00:35:45,680
Even the police can't do anything.

756
00:35:45,680 --> 00:35:47,000
What can I possibly do?

757
00:35:47,000 --> 00:35:47,960
Idiot.

758
00:35:49,120 --> 00:35:51,000
Let us in.

759
00:35:52,720 --> 00:35:53,560
Here's the thing.

760
00:35:53,960 --> 00:35:55,520
Go hook up the loudspeaker outside.

761
00:35:56,000 --> 00:35:57,160
They can listen outside.

762
00:35:57,720 --> 00:35:59,320
Won't that cause even more chaos?

763
00:35:59,320 --> 00:36:00,320
Just go do it.

764
00:36:00,320 --> 00:36:01,720
All right.

765
00:36:02,040 --> 00:36:03,040
It's full.

766
00:36:03,040 --> 00:36:04,840
Come back tomorrow.

767
00:36:04,840 --> 00:36:06,000
Come on.

768
00:36:06,000 --> 00:36:07,320
Line up on both sides.

769
00:36:07,320 --> 00:36:10,080
♪Honghu waters, long and long♪

770
00:36:10,520 --> 00:36:13,600
♪The people's hearts turn
toward the Party♪

771
00:36:13,810 --> 00:36:16,890
♪He Long led the revolution♪

772
00:36:16,890 --> 00:36:19,490
♪Red flags flutter, winning the battles♪

773
00:36:19,490 --> 00:36:22,500
(Best wishes to the premiere)

774
00:36:22,500 --> 00:36:25,970
♪Women took up blades
to defend their homes♪

775
00:36:25,970 --> 00:36:28,910
♪Red Guard members
stepped forward bravely♪

776
00:36:28,910 --> 00:36:30,960
♪With shared hatred,
they headed to the battlefield♪

777
00:36:30,960 --> 00:36:31,800
They've calmed down.

778
00:36:33,320 --> 00:36:34,360
When you do things,

779
00:36:34,680 --> 00:36:36,520
you've got to pay attention to methods.

780
00:36:37,293 --> 00:36:39,320
There are always more solutions
than difficulties.

781
00:36:39,600 --> 00:36:40,960
We've got to use our brains.

782
00:36:41,360 --> 00:36:42,200
Right.

783
00:36:42,920 --> 00:36:45,080
As expected,
you do have work experience.

784
00:36:47,920 --> 00:36:49,240
We haven't seen a scene like this

785
00:36:49,880 --> 00:36:52,640
in many years.

786
00:36:53,280 --> 00:36:54,160
Zhu,

787
00:36:54,680 --> 00:36:56,040
I have a hunch.

788
00:36:57,040 --> 00:36:59,760
Tonight, our cannon blast

789
00:37:00,280 --> 00:37:02,320
is probably going to make a big noise.

790
00:37:03,400 --> 00:37:04,240
Right.

791
00:37:05,120 --> 00:37:06,560
An instant hit.

792
00:37:17,840 --> 00:37:19,240
Look at Chu Jiahe's hand.

793
00:37:19,240 --> 00:37:20,240
It's shaking.

794
00:37:21,280 --> 00:37:22,280
Could she be scared?

795
00:37:22,280 --> 00:37:23,680
Your local tunes sound lovely.

796
00:37:23,691 --> 00:37:25,425
- With so many people here,
- Call them up.

797
00:37:25,436 --> 00:37:26,442
I'm even scared for her.

798
00:37:26,453 --> 00:37:28,790
To add a bit of elegance for our leader.

799
00:37:28,790 --> 00:37:29,680
Sure.

800
00:37:29,890 --> 00:37:31,400
Sir, what would you like to hear?

801
00:37:31,400 --> 00:37:32,960
Just sing anything.

802
00:37:32,960 --> 00:37:35,360
- Don't be nervous.
- Just sing anything.

803
00:37:36,400 --> 00:37:37,606
- Don't be nervous.
- Singers.

804
00:37:38,080 --> 00:37:39,010
Come in.

805
00:37:41,120 --> 00:37:41,960
Go.

806
00:37:41,960 --> 00:37:43,740
Singers, sing well.

807
00:37:44,170 --> 00:37:45,180
If you sing well,

808
00:37:45,430 --> 00:37:47,510
our leader will give you a reward.

809
00:38:08,060 --> 00:38:11,420
(Build socialism with greater, faster,
better, and more economical results)

810
00:38:25,520 --> 00:38:26,840
Little girl,

811
00:38:27,400 --> 00:38:31,800
a little tune is easy to sing,
but hard to start.

812
00:38:38,400 --> 00:38:40,520
A little country girl,

813
00:38:40,520 --> 00:38:42,080
who hasn't seen the world,

814
00:38:42,080 --> 00:38:43,920
seeing such a high-ranking official
as you,

815
00:38:43,920 --> 00:38:45,720
is too scared to sing.

816
00:38:46,320 --> 00:38:48,040
Very good, very good.

817
00:38:51,000 --> 00:38:52,000
Little girl,

818
00:38:52,520 --> 00:38:53,960
sing boldly.

819
00:38:54,520 --> 00:39:00,040
Pick up the saucer in your hands
and start playing.

820
00:39:18,920 --> 00:39:20,360
I'm all sweaty from anxiety.

821
00:39:25,160 --> 00:39:26,920
Experience solves it.

822
00:39:30,340 --> 00:39:35,680
(Best wishes to the premiere)

823
00:39:35,680 --> 00:39:39,910
♪Gentlemen and officers,
listen with pleasure♪

824
00:39:39,910 --> 00:39:48,420
♪The shores of Honghu are my home♪

825
00:39:48,720 --> 00:39:53,130
♪Boats set out at dawn
to cast their nets♪

826
00:39:53,130 --> 00:40:10,530
♪Returning in the evening
with holds full of fish♪

827
00:40:26,280 --> 00:40:28,240
That's more than during the rehearsal.

828
00:40:29,080 --> 00:40:29,920
This cannon blast

829
00:40:30,200 --> 00:40:32,600
is a continuation
of the October Revolution's cannon fire.

830
00:40:32,960 --> 00:40:34,840
The director said
it must be earth-shaking.

831
00:40:36,560 --> 00:40:37,680
Keep it under control.

832
00:40:38,200 --> 00:40:39,720
Not only is it under control,

833
00:40:39,720 --> 00:40:41,279
but there's a ball of fire in my heart.

834
00:40:41,360 --> 00:40:43,000
It's about to suffocate me.

835
00:42:21,320 --> 00:42:22,400
Try to open up a bit.

836
00:42:23,920 --> 00:42:25,080
In the world of opera,

837
00:42:26,160 --> 00:42:28,360
singers always take turns,

838
00:42:29,040 --> 00:42:30,480
taking a foreign land for one's home.

839
00:42:32,440 --> 00:42:34,400
No one can stand on stage
for a lifetime.

840
00:42:47,480 --> 00:42:49,400
I'm going to a foreign land tomorrow.

841
00:42:52,680 --> 00:42:53,720
You'll go have the baby?

842
00:42:54,840 --> 00:42:55,680
I'll go take

843
00:42:57,920 --> 00:43:02,200
a foreign land for my home.

844
00:43:05,020 --> 00:43:06,940
=The Lead=
(Preview)

845
00:43:09,400 --> 00:43:12,360
Aim at the enemy! Fire!

846
00:43:19,560 --> 00:43:21,280
Go to the hospital now! An emergency!

847
00:43:21,280 --> 00:43:23,400
Hu Sanyuan's current condition
is very bad.

848
00:43:23,400 --> 00:43:24,520
He needs emergency treatment.

849
00:43:24,600 --> 00:43:26,320
Is Ding Zhisheng's family here?

850
00:43:26,440 --> 00:43:27,280
He's gone.

851
00:43:28,920 --> 00:43:30,560
Hu Sanyuan did it on purpose.

852
00:43:30,680 --> 00:43:32,000
He's making it worse.

853
00:43:32,000 --> 00:43:33,600
He wants Hu Sanyuan dead.

854
00:43:37,000 --> 00:43:41,620
♪When I woke up and turned back♪

855
00:43:43,090 --> 00:43:47,930
♪I wasn't sure where to go♪

856
00:43:49,370 --> 00:43:53,560
♪We met and brushed past♪

857
00:43:55,120 --> 00:44:02,420
♪Your shadow drifted out of sight♪

858
00:44:16,790 --> 00:44:20,540
♪The stove fire blazed in my dream♪

859
00:44:22,140 --> 00:44:27,710
♪Lit up the tracks of pearly tears♪

860
00:44:28,830 --> 00:44:32,890
♪In my dream, water sleeves flew♪

861
00:44:34,020 --> 00:44:39,610
♪Hiding a lifetime of love♪

862
00:44:40,770 --> 00:44:44,970
♪The Qinling Mountains
crossed the stage♪

863
00:44:46,010 --> 00:44:51,640
♪Spring water brewed strong wine♪

864
00:44:52,810 --> 00:44:57,500
♪Sheep moved through the valley♪

865
00:44:58,180 --> 00:45:03,350
♪It felt like a promise
from another life♪

866
00:45:04,020 --> 00:45:09,050
♪When I woke up and turned back♪

867
00:45:10,080 --> 00:45:15,510
♪I wasn't sure where to go♪

868
00:45:15,890 --> 00:45:21,170
♪If I chose again, I'd still roam♪

869
00:45:22,120 --> 00:45:27,930
♪All over this sunlit plateau♪

870
00:45:27,930 --> 00:45:33,350
♪The dream ends; the curtain falls♪

871
00:45:33,900 --> 00:45:39,410
♪Moonlight washes off this stage makeup♪

872
00:45:39,960 --> 00:45:44,920
♪The one in the mirror wears gray hair♪

873
00:45:45,940 --> 00:45:51,220
♪Already sang all my joy and sorrow♪

874
00:45:52,020 --> 00:46:01,050
♪Already shouted across Qinchuan Plain♪
